node.text: The ankles are very often overlooked when trying to improve squatting mechanics. Give this a try! Any dull stainless steel tool can work (back of a knife or similar) but @sidekicktool takes it to another level!!

node.text:
Protein icecream FTW

150g frozen banana
150ml almond milk (unsweetened)
25g @foodspring_athletics 3K chocolate protein
Sweetener to taste (vanilla)
Optional - peanut butter / peanut butter powder. 

Mix all ingredients and put in freezer - stir frequently to avoid crystallization. 

My favorite snack!

node.text:
I was nervous to start the competing yesterday …. It has been a long time since I’ve stepped onto the competition floor. Not knowing where I stand with the other girls and a different build up to the Games than any other year brought a lot of doubt and fear of being inadequate. 

But I told myself this: “Annie, you have worked your ass off the last 12 months and you deserve to let yourself show it on the competition floor.”

Day 1 is done and dusted and I’m very proud of my performance and effort.  I didn’t leave anything in the tank on E1, E2 and E4. E3 I let “the little monkey” inside my head get the best of me. I told myself “ I don’t know how fast I can go, the others are probably so much faster because I haven’t been running that much.  I just don’t want to be last” 

At this level of competition, you can’t doubt your ability. You have to push to find the threshold and if the wheels come off, well you try your best with what you have left. 

The CrossFit games are as much mental as it is physical. 

Just giving you a glimpse of some of the things that still happen even though this is my 11th time competing here. 

No more doubt !  No more excuses ! 

I will just let myself GO and have fun in the process. 
#enjoythejourney #dottir #mentalgame #letgo #nodoubt #lovewhatyoudo

Today was AMAZING. 

I swam further than I’ve ever swam before. I ran faster than I’ve run in more than 2 years and I got to meet THE COLISEUM again for the first time since 2018 - and it did not disappoint. Rest day tomorrow and then three more days to put our fitness to the test! 

#fitness #enjoythejourney #dottir #mother #electric #loud #goodtobehome

node.text:
Only two more sleeps until the kickoff of the 2021 @crossfitgames. 

The last 12 months have been more challenging than any other period in my life. At the same time it has also been the BEST 12 months of my life without ANY doubt. 

I’m going into my 11th CrossFit Games in 13 seasons. ‘13 I missed due to injury, ‘20 due to pregnancy. I hope at the end of this weekend, 2014 (🥈) and 2021 (?) will stand out as two of my proudest years. 

It’s easy to smile when the road is easy, but the most rewarding wins are won when you have to FIGHT. 

This year I’m doing it for Freyja AND myself - proving that you can do whatever you put your mind to. Work hard and be proud. 

3…2…1… GO! Let’s do this.. #motherhood #dottir #enjoythejourney #lovewhatyoudo #crossfit

Last dose of high intensity before it all starts on Wednesday! 

The work has been put in - now we recover and get ready to RACE! 

#enjoythejourney #fitness #crossfit #hiit #crossfitgames #excited #dottir #motherhood #reebok

node.text:
Almost every single morning is the same for me. It starts with @transparentlabs collagen protein, greens powder and creatine about 30min before I have breakfast. 

I’m doing everything I can to give my body the best chance to heal up after having Freyja - AND to recover from a little training for the @crossfitgames

What is your morning routine?

 #fitness #mom #athlete #recovery #swimsuit #allsmiles #enjoythejourney #greattaste

node.text:
What to eat when traveling?? Well, it doesn’t have to be complicated thanks to @rpstrength. 

Even more so now than ever you’ll have to PLAN AHEAD. 

1kg of chicken, 
500g rice and a 
HUUUGE mixed salad is going to keep me and @frederikaegidius fueled for the trip to MADISON AND THE CROSSFIT GAMES!

If you don’t have the option of cooking a lot before heading out here are my go to options for travel foods:

Boiled eggs, not the best for the person sitting next to you but it will clear TSA. 

Fresh fruits, full of good carbs and nutrients - make sure to finish them before leaving the plane if flying overseas :)

Nuts: every airport will have plenty of high fat snacks, but a bag of nuts is always a good choice if you can stick to just that one serving. 

Shy away from the quick fix sandwiches and other high processed foods - your stomach will thank you and you’ll arrive feeling better.
#travel #nutrition #protip #protein #carbs #fats #macros #food
